en_179928_0	The fire which erupted in the Meethotamulla garbage mound yesterday (Jan. 01) is believed to have been caused by a chemical reaction.
en_179928_1	A spokesperson from the Colombo Fire Brigade stated that Methane could be the reason for the fire.
en_179928_2	He said although the fire was completely doused by 3 pm yesterday, smoke is still emitting intermittently from the garbage mound.
en_179928_3	Meanwhile, police have asked the Government Analyst, Geological and Mining Bureau and Urban Development Authority and several other respective organizations to conduct investigations into the fire.
en_179928_4	Police Media Spokesperson Office said that several police teams have been deployed in Meethotamulla and the surrounding areas due to the prevailing situation.
